<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-528-224  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 528 224.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>InfoWorld  August 14 1989 v11 n33 p8(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Mitem toolkit lets Hypercard front for host. (Mitemview) (productannouncement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Flynn, Laurie.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Mitem Corp introduces Mitemview, a software toolkit that helpsdevelopers devise Hypercard front ends to mainframe hosts withoutmodifying the host code.andP;  The product enables access to data onthe mainframes, protecting the investment in both the informationand the hardware.andP;  Watch Host Operating Patterns (Whoop), aproprietary pattern-recognition technology, is the heart of theprogram.andP;  It resides between an intelligent Hypercard stack andlinks the user to one or more applications and host interfacemodules.andP;  Whoop provides a view of what the user needs in the hostand spots relevant patterns quickly.andP;  A $995 entry-level versionis scheduled to ship Sep 1989.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Mitem Corp. (product introduction).andO;Product:   Mitemview (Program development software) (product introduction)Hypercard (Data base management system) (computer programs).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionSoftware PackagesProgram Development ToolsMicro-Mainframe Communication.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>